<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Arbitrage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> de Jong, A., L. Rosenthal and M.A. van Dijk, 2008, The Risk and Return of Arbitrage in Dual-Listed Companies, June 2008.<a href="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=525282" class="external autonumber" title="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=525282" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Lowenstein, R., 2000, When genius failed: The rise and fall of Long-Term Capital Management, Random House.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFNed_Potter2006">Ned Potter (2006-10-13). <a href="http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=2560255" class="external text" title="http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=2560255" rel="nofollow">"Free International Calls! Just Dial ... Iowa"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=2560255" class="external free" title="http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=2560255" rel="nofollow">http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=2560255</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-23</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Free+International+Calls%21+Just+Dial+...+Iowa&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Ned+Potter&amp;rft.au=Ned+Potter&amp;rft.date=2006-10-13&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FTechnology%2Fstory%3Fid%3D2560255&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Arbitrage"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMike_Masnick2007">Mike Masnick (2007-02-07). <a href="http://techdirt.com/articles/20070207/123022.shtml" class="external text" title="http://techdirt.com/articles/20070207/123022.shtml" rel="nofollow">"Phone Call Arbitrage Is All Fun And Games (And Profit) Until AT&amp;T Hits You With A $2 Million Lawsuit"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://techdirt.com/articles/20070207/123022.shtml" class="external free" title="http://techdirt.com/articles/20070207/123022.shtml" rel="nofollow">http://techdirt.com/articles/20070207/123022.shtml</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-23</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Phone+Call+Arbitrage+Is+All+Fun+And+Games+%28And+Profit%29+Until+AT%26T+Hits+You+With+A+%242+Million+Lawsuit&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mike+Masnick&amp;rft.au=Mike+Masnick&amp;rft.date=2007-02-07&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ftechdirt.com%2Farticles%2F20070207%2F123022.shtml&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Arbitrage"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
